      "raw": "# AI Intelligence Briefing - June 16, 2026\n*Curated from knowledge graph (125 nodes, 145 edges) · All articles published within the last 7 days*\n\n• **Colleges Must Act Now to Regain Public Trust, AAC&U Says** — A new report urges colleges to address trust gaps and engage communities.\n  🔗 Graph: brett-pollak, ai-governance, higher-ed-ai\n  📅 Published: 2026-06-16\n  📰 https://www.insidehighered.com/news/institutions/2026/06/16/colleges-must-act-now-regain-public-trust-aacu-says\n  📌 Key takeaways:\n    • Gallup poll shows public confidence in higher education rose to 42% after a decade low.\n    • AAC&U attributes low trust to lack of trustworthiness and recommends accountability and community partnerships.\n    • Leaders should proactively demonstrate institutional value to both enrolled students and the broader public.\n    • Trust is framed as essential to resist political attacks on institutional independence.\n\n• **Common App Adds AI Advising Tool** — The Common App integrates College Possible’s AI advisor to aid students.\n  🔗 Graph: brett-pollak, higher-ed-ai, ai-adoption\n  📅 Published: 2026-06-16\n  📰 https://www.insidehighered.com/news/student-success/academic-life/2026/06/16/common-app-adds-ai-advising-tool\n  📌 Key takeaways:\n    • Partnership brings College Possible’s Coach Possible AI to the Common App platform.\n    • AI tool offers 24/7 support for application navigation, deadline tracking, and enrollment guidance.\n    • Advisers can monitor student activity to target additional help where needed.\n    • Aims to reduce barriers for first‑generation and low‑income applicants.\n\n• **The data center is the new football stadium. Are you ready to build one?** — Data‑center capacity becomes a strategic priority for research universities.\n  🔗 Graph: tritonai, data-analytics, onyx\n  📅 Published: 2026-06-16\n  📰 https://universitybusiness.com/the-data-center-is-the-new-football-stadium-are-you-ready-to-build-one/\n  📌 Key takeaways:\n    • AI‑intensive research drives demand for high‑power data‑center infrastructure (60‑100 kW per rack).\n    • Facilities investment is now a recruitment, revenue, and talent‑retention lever for universities.\n    • Liquid‑cooling technologies are becoming essential for AI workloads.\n    • Donors and faculty increasingly evaluate institutions on compute capability.\n\n💡 Signal: Higher‑education leaders are confronting AI‑driven trust, admissions support, and infrastructure challenges, highlighting the strategic importance of AI governance, adoption, and compute resources.\n"
